data.description: This lovingly maintained single-owner home is situated on a 1.2-acre lot within a quiet cul-de-sac in the Preserve at Southcreek, providing a peaceful and spacious environment. The kitchen is designed with a chef in mind, featuring double wall ovens, a gas stove top, and a large island that's great for entertaining. The den is open to the kitchen and offers the cozy warmth of a gas fireplace, making it a comfortable space for relaxation. The three-season porch is a great spot for enjoying your morning coffee and connecting to the outdoors. The upper level of the home includes four beds and two baths, including the Primary bedroom with two walk-in closets and its own ensuite bath. The home boasts a full walk-out basement, which adds additional living space and includes another room and a full bathroom. The outdoor area is spacious and includes a detached shed. The front and rear yards have irrigation systems to help maintain the landscape. Don't worry about losing power! The home has whole house generator fueled by natural gas. The property's location is advantageous for commuters, as it's just minutes from Interstate 95, offering easy access to Richmond and the surrounding areas.
